    "<p>Harvard professor and director of the Walters Art Gallery and Cleveland Museum of Art.": [],
    "Bergman attended Rutgers University undergraduate, graduating in 1966.": [],
    "His master's degree, 1969 and Ph.D., 1972, were both awarded from Princeton University.": [],
    "He received Fulbright and Guggenheim fellowships.": [],
    "His dissertation, written under <a href=\"/weitzmannk\">Kurt Weitzmann</a> was on the Salerno Ivories.": [],
    "In 1971 he taught as an assistant at Princeton, joining Harvard in 1976 as associate professor of fine arts.": [
